data.value:
LOLA has been optimised for mobile usage on the following devices: Samsung S10 (360x740 px), iPhoneX (375x812 px), Samsung Galaxy S7 (360x640 px), iPhone8 (375x667 px), iPad PRO (1024x1366 px), iPad2 (768x1024 px). Web browsers: Google Chrome for Windows and Safari for iOS

The data acquired by Fom Industrie s.r.l. using the LO.LA application will be stored and handled for statistical purposes only, and will not be passed on to third parties. As this is not personal information, it is not subject to the contents of EU Regulation 2016/679.

LIMITS OF LIABILITY

The reliability of information displayed in LOLA is also conditional on the Licensee “resetting” the counter values if these play an independent role in the replacement of a machine component. Consequently, when management and maintenance of so-called consumable components/components subject to wear is carried out by the licensee (for example replacement of tools, changing or sharpening blades, changing labelling unit rolls, etc.), reset of the indicators must be carried out by the Licensee when the associated physical component is replaced. Consequently, the Licensor shall not be considered responsible in any way in the event of missing and/or late warnings by the LOLA software if the data indicated above has not been duly reset in the machine software by the Licensee. Instructions on how to carry out the “reset” can be found in the LOLA user manual.

The Licensor is, likewise, not to be held liable in any way for breakages, machine stoppage, production stoppage, etc., in the event that the Licensee decides not to carry out the operations recommended by the LOLA software, indicated by means of ordinary and/or predictive maintenance notices (e.g. changing oil and lubricants).

The Licensor provides no guarantee that the Service will be suitable for particular purposes: no liability shall be assigned him if supply of the Service, with the precise characteristics requested by the Licensee, is conditional to Third Party or Licensee events.

The program incorporates a database containing technical information detected by the numerical control for the specific machine, identified using its production number (serial number). The Licensor cannot exclude the presence of errors or omissions and is not responsible for any damage caused to the Licensee or to third parties as a result of said errors or omissions. In any event the Licensee is invited to report any problems, malfunctions, inabilities to access the service to the e-mail address support@fomservice.com

The Licensor shall not be liable in any way for damage suffered by the Licensee, either directly or indirectly, as a result of using the Service or of failure to carry out ordinary maintenance as indicated in the User and Maintenance Manual and/or suggested by the Licensor on the machine in which the Service is installed, except in the case of wilful misconduct or gross negligence.

The Licensor engages to ensure that the Service operates as well as possible, but does not take on any responsibility for delays, suspensions and/or interruptions in delivery of the update services due to causes that cannot be attributed to him, a non-limiting example of which might be:

data.name: AskCredentialTitle
data.value: I can’t access LOLA, I can’t remember my username and password

data.name: AskCredentialBody
data.value:
If you are a user with a “Customer” role (Fom Industrie VIPAREA user), use the access credentials you received by email. If you do not remember your password, open the URL below and click on LOST PASSWORD:
http://viparea.fomindustrie.com/areaVip.aspx

If you are a LOLA user (Operator/Head Workshop role), check that your manager has sent you an email and/or printout of this type, containing your username and provisional access password.

data.name: HowToUseTitle
data.value: I can access LOLA but I don't know how to use it

data.name: HowToUseBody
data.value:
Access the FOM Industrie VIPAREA and download the LOLA user manual for your machine tool.
http://viparea.fomindustrie.com/areaVip.aspx

data.name: NoMachineVisibleBody
data.value:
If the license has only just been activated, make sure that your Fom Industrie machine tool’s PC is connected to the internet and that the HMI SW (FST CUT or FST CAM or FST LINE) is open on the machine’s PC.
Please contact your network Administrator to enable the following sites to be reached, from the machine:
https://viparea.fomindustrie.com
https://lola.fomindustrie.com
https://lolaapi.fomindustrie.com
If not, connect to the internet and run the FST SW, then check LOLA again to see if the data is visible.

data.name: NoMachineVisibleTitle
data.value: I can access LOLA but I can’t see any machines

data.name: NoMachineVisibleTitle2
data.value: I can access LOLA, my machine’s PC is connected to the internet, the SW is open, but I can’t see any machines in LOLA

data.name: NoMachineVisibleBody2
data.value:
If your machine’s LOLA license was not activated recently, check that it has not expired. If more than one license has been purchased, check the expiry date of the LOLA license for each machine, by accessing VIPAREA:
http://viparea.fomindustrie.com/areaVip.aspx
If the license for one or more machines has expired, purchase and/or renew the LOLA license by selecting the machine in question and then proceeding to payment of the license. After this has been done, access LOLA again to check.

data.name: NoDataFromMachineTitle
data.value: I have checked points 1, 2 and 3 but I am still not receiving data from the machine

data.name: NoDataFromMachineBody
data.value:
If the problems persist, please send a LOLA support request:
  • by telephone on + 39 0541 832 777 (FOM Service hotline)
  • by sending an e-mail to support@fomservice.com
indicating:
  1. your VIPAREA username, e.g. usr0043
  2. serial number of the machine for which the LOLA license has been activated
  3. preferred time you wish to be contacted

data.name: OtherProblemTitle
data.value: My problem is not among the ones listed

data.name: OtherProblemBody
data.value: Send a service request by filling in the form found in the menu under the item “Support”, if possible attaching a screenshot to describe the problem.
